cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image embeddings and their use in semantic image retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of WordNet, a lexical database, to encode prior world-knowledge, which suggests a possible connection to natural language processing and thus cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a deterministic algorithm for computing class centroids, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential use of these embeddings for novelty detection and few-shot learning, which could relate to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
